


java have 3 editions
-java standard edition(JSE)- for developing apps which not need server and DB(calculator)
-java enterprice edition(J2EE)- for developing apps which need server(websites)
-java micro edition(J2ME)- for developing mobile apps 

java enterprice edition is used for wed developmentt but it have following issues
-EJB (Enterprise Java Beans) these are hard to configure 
-so spring is introduced
-spring boot gives a embedded server named tomcat
-spring boot all the configiration and result ready deplay apps


features
Inversion of control:it is an approuch for handling objects and maintain configurable apps 
-we not need to create objects for classes manually using bean
-bean is a simple java obj 
